title: For Sale:  Vintage Herter’s Model 81 Press
postcontent:
Up for sale is a unique vintage Herter’s Model 81 dual ram press and 21 of the Herter’s matching shell holders as a package deal for $125. I will not separate. Made of real cast iron it’s definitely heavy duty construction and in decent shape overall. I disassembled it and cleaned it up a bit and lubed all the moving parts. The top is threaded for standard size 7/8-14 dies and the rams have what appear to be homemade shell holder adaptors to fit current standard shell holders. I do not have the priming arm or primer catcher cup. It was designed to process 2 pieces of brass in a single stroke, or as a swaging press for increased production.
There has been some questions over the price, The Herter’s shell adaptors run about $4ea average on sites such as eBay so $4x21=$84 with the balance going towards the press.
